# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in. The HF scripts auto-load it
# via _env.py — no need to `export` on every shell.
#
#   cd router/scripts
#   cp .env.example .env
#   # edit .env, paste your token (or leave blank for download-only)
#
# When you actually need HF_TOKEN:
#   * download_from_hf.py: NEVER required — the model repo is public.
#     Leave HF_TOKEN blank or unset.
#   * upload_to_hf.py: required, with **Write** scope on the target
#     HF org (default: weave-eng). Self-hosters running their own
#     fork only need this if they're pushing to their own HF repo.
#
# Mint at https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens — name the token
# after its consumer (e.g. "steven-laptop") so you can revoke it
# independently.

HF_TOKEN=
